se.jguru.nazgul.core.algorithms.api.trees.path

Interface SemanticPath<E extends Enum<E>,SegmentType extends Serializable & Comparable<SegmentType>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<Path<SegmentType>>, Iterable<SegmentType>, Path<SegmentType>, Serializable

    public interface SemanticPath<E extends Enum<E>,SegmentType extends Serializable & Comparable<SegmentType>>
extends Path<SegmentType>
    An extension to Path where all segments have a semantic meaning, defined by the values of an Enum. This implies that all levels of the path correspond to some concept, and that the SemanticPath in essence works as a Map relating Enum values to SegmentType values.
    Author:
    Lennart Jörelid, jGuru Europe AB

      • getMaxSize

        int getMaxSize()
        Returns:
        The maximum number of segments in this Path, typically identical to the number of values in the semantic definition Enum.

      • get

        SegmentType get(E semanticDefinition)
        Retrieves the SegmentType segment corresponding to the Enum value providing the semantic definition of this SemanticPath.
        Parameters:
        semanticDefinition - The semantic definition within this SemanticPath whose value should be retrieved.
        Returns:
        The segment corresponding to the provided semantic definition, or null if no segment SegmentType is defined for the provided semanticDefinition level within this SemanticPath.
